oot drips Saprolings on **each** upkeep, not just yours) and resolve Craterhoof Behemoth (MV 8 with {5}{G}{G}{G} \u2014 note Craterhoof cannot be cascaded into)."}, {"name": "Ghalta + Eldrazi pile", "tag": "T5\u20137", "note": "Ghalta Primal Hunger costs {10}{G}{G} reduced by total power of creatures you control (floor {G}{G})."}, {"name": "Ulamog Ceaseless mill", "tag": "T8+", "note": "Hardcast Ulamog Ceaseless Hunger ({10})."}, {"name": "Sunbird's Invocation chain", "tag": "T6+", "note": "Resolve Sunbird's Invocation."}], "rulings": [{"name": "Cascade requires MV strictly less than 8.", "note": "Wanderer cannot cascade into the Eldrazi titans (Ulamogs 10/11, Kozileks 10), Craterhoof (8), or Ghalta (12) \u2014 those must be hardcast. It can hit Avenger (7), Etali (6), Selvala's Stampede (6), and lower."}, {"name": "Sunbird's Invocation triggers ONLY on spells cast from hand", "note": "cascade hits, Aetherworks / Etali / Creative Technique free-casts, and Selvala's Stampede ETBs do NOT trigger it."}, {"name": "Both Ulamogs are indestructible", "note": "(survive non-exile wipes). Ulamog Infinite Gyre and Kozilek Butcher self-shuffle from the graveyard; Ulamog Ceaseless Hunger does NOT self-recur \u2014 once milled or exiled it's gone, so hardcast it or keep it in hand."}, {"name": "Void Winnower", "note": "while it's on the battlefield, opponents can't cast even-MV spells (2/4/6 removal and counters) AND can't block with even-MV creatures."}, {"name": "Conduit of Worlds is one-spell-per-turn-total", "note": "when you grave-cast (not a bonus cast), and only at sorcery speed if you haven't cast a spell yet that turn."}, {"name": "Creative Technique's Demonstrate lets an opponent copy it too", "note": "(you resolve first)."}, {"name": "Decimate needs a legal target in all four categories", "note": "(artifact + creature + enchantment + land) or it can't be cast."}], "composition": [{"name": "Cascade & Free-Cast Engines", "count": 9, "win": false}, {"name": "Power-Matters